title: Spallation of vanadium, manganese and cobalt with 187 MeV protons.

x4freetext: Spallation of vanadium, manganese and cobalt with
187 MeV protons.

flag.hlp: Reference to related data compiled in another entry

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Journal of Inorganic and Nuclear Chemistry, Vol.19, p.1 (1961)

x4freetext: sb
The target materials were analysed chemically-V, Mn,Co
and spectroscopically-vanadium.
Corrections had to applied to the counting rates for
coincidence losses, background activity, geometrical
differences, absorption in the window and in the air
between the sample and the window, backscattering,
self-absorption and self-scattering, counting
efficiency, chemical yield and decay.

x4freetext: for comparison
*By authors*.In most of the vanadium bombardments the
nuclide V-48 was used as a monitor. The absolute cross
section of this monitor was determined by comparing the
yield of it with the yield of Na-24 from an Al-foil
covering the same area as the target.
.Computed from the amount of V-48 formed
.Uncertain since the activity of Na-22 was low
